enedione to testosterone","Converts testosterone to dihydrotestosterone","Converts progesterone to testosterone"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe enzyme 5-alpha reductase primarily \u003Cstrong\u003Econverts testosterone to dihydrotestosterone\u003C/strong\u003E. This conversion is essential for normal male sexual development, particularly the development of external genitalia during embryogenesis and prostate growth during puberty and adulthood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are explained below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConverts testosterone to oestradiol\u003C/strong\u003E: this is the action of the aromatase enzyme, which is important for oestrogen synthesis in both males and females\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConverts dihydrotestosterone to testosterone\u003C/strong\u003E: this conversion is not physiologically possible as the reaction is irreversible; dihydrotestosterone cannot be converted back to testosterone\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConverts androstenedione to testosterone\u003C/strong\u003E: this conversion is catalysed by 17-beta hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase in the steroid synthesis pathway\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConverts progesterone to testosterone\u003C/strong\u003E: the conversion of progesterone to testosterone requires multiple enzymatic steps including 17-alpha-hydroxylase and 17,20-lyase\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this enzyme\u0027s action is clinically important as 5-alpha reductase inhibitors like finasteride are used to treat conditions such as benign prostatic hyperplasia and male pattern baldness by reducing dihydrotestosterone levels.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["5-alpha reductase converts testosterone to dihydrotestosterone, which is essential for male sexual development and prostate growth.","5-alpha reductase inhibitors like finasteride and dutasteride are used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia and androgenetic alopecia.","Blocking 5-alpha reductase reduces dihydrotestosterone levels while maintaining normal testosterone levels."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52423"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16464"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52423"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T09:28:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T09:29:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9155"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66969"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","lin